This aerial view shows the Johannesburg skyline and the Bree taxi rank in Newtown, Johannesburg, on May 7, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - People who purchased homes before the lockdown will be allowed to relocate and move their goods. These are regulations published and gazetted by Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma. This also includes new lease agreements and businesses moving to new premises. However, travel across provincial, metropolitan, or district boundaries will require a permit from the police. Movers are urged to adhere to COVID-19 regulations and directives issued by the transport minister. Those moving should do so between 7 May and 7 June. This will be a once-off movement. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.